Ventrue: The "Clan of Kings," aristocratic leaders and business tycoons.
Toreador: The "Clan of the Rose," obsessed with art, beauty, and human emotion.
Tremere: Blood sorcerers who use Thaumaturgy to manipulate reality.
Malkavian: Seers and lunatics connected by a shared madness called the Malkavian Madness Network.
Nosferatu: Hideously deformed information brokers who dwell in the shadows.
Banu Haqim: Formerly known as Assamites, they are judges and assassins.
Lasombra: Masters of shadow and darkness, formerly the leaders of the Sabbat. 
Brujah: Rebels and firebrands who fight against perceived injustice.
Gangrel: Primal survivors with a deep connection to their animalistic side.
The Ministry: Formerly the Followers of Set, they are tempters and corrupters.
Ravnos: Tricksters and illusionists who lead a nomadic, risky unlife. 
Hecata: The "Clan of Death," a modern union of necromantic families like the Giovanni and Cappadocians.
Tzimisce: Transhumanist flesh-sculptors and territorial lords.
Salubri: A rare, hunted lineage distinguished by a third eye and a focus on healing or soul-guarding. 
